      },
      "modified": "1970-01-01T00:00:00.008Z",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "**The lower-right herbal form.** A bulbous green cabbage-like figure with small nude women clustered at its base — visually unlike the page's main top figure, more reminiscent of the herbal quire. Multi-figure pages like this blur the manuscript's quire boundaries: the categories herbal / balneological / cosmological were imposed by later scholars and don't always match how the original scribe partitioned content.",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        }
      ],
